Just g++ main.cxx, right?; >; > In that case XRootD would be picked up from /usr. Which doesn't tell us; > much about our problem. Since RD's test job will pick up XRootD from:; >; > /cvmfs/atlas.cern.ch/repo/sw/software/21.2/AnalysisBaseExternals/21.2.139/InstallArea/x86_64-centos7-gcc8-opt/lib/; >; > This is why I said at the beginning, that I'm suspicious about the; > LD_PRELOAD setting. If that library wants to use XRootD, but it was; > compiled against a different version of XRootD than what the analysis; > release comes with, then we're in trouble. Note that *all* ATLAS releases; > come with their own version of XRootD, not just the analysis releases.
